# 1. 新しい服を求めて

Delivery Person: Alright, if you'll excuse me!
Kanade: Thank you.
Kanade: Here we...go...
Kanade: Phew... When was the last time I bought new clothes like this?
Kanade: (I was bought that jacket when I was still in junior high school. It was so comfortable that I ended up wearing it until I poked a hole in one of the pockets...)
Kanade: I tried ordering something that had good reviews online, so let's see...
Kanade: Huh...?
Kanade: It's not as warm as I'd hoped...
Kanade: I think I made a mistake...
Kanade: (What do I do? It's been really cold lately, so I'd like to have a new jacket handy...)
Kanade: (But it's going to take time for whatever I order to get delivered. Plus, I don't want to get the wrong thing again...)
Kanade: Looks like I'm left with no choice but to go to the store...
Kanade: I'm visiting Dad tomorrow, so... I can stop by the mall on my way home.
Kanade: Oh, it's so cold...
Kanade: (I'll quickly buy a jacket and head straight home.)
Kanade: (There's a bit of a crowd, but I should be able to use this street as a shortcut to get to the mall.)
New Hairstylist: Oh, you there! Hello!
Kanade: ...?
New Hairstylist: Do you happen to have some time right now?
Kanade: Wait, are you talking to me...?
New Hairstylist: Yes! Would you be interested in becoming a haircut model?
Kanade: A haircut model...?
New Hairstylist: Yes, I work at the salon just over there!
New Hairstylist: The second I saw your gorgeous hair, I just knew I had to ask you!
Kanade: No, I...
New Hairstylist: Oh, your haircut will be free of charge! You'll even get whatever hair treatments you like.
Kanade: (Th-That's a really generous offer, but... What should I do...?)
Kanade: (If I go to the salon, I might not have enough energy left to go buy a new jacket...)
???: Kanade!
Kanade: Huh?
Saki: Thanks for waiting. And sorry I'm late...!
Kanade: Tenma...?
New Hairstylist: Oh, you were waiting for your friend...! I apologize for interrupting.
Saki: No, you don't need to apologize!
New Hairstylist: But here's the salon's card. Please consider stopping by later if you're interested!
Saki: Thank you♪ Anyway, let's go!
Kanade: Huh? Uhh... O-Okay...
Saki: So... I'm really sorry about just now!
Kanade: Huh...?
Saki: You looked like you were in trouble, Kanade... I mean, Yoisaki... That's why I thought I had to step in and help...
Saki: I hope I didn't get the wrong idea...
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: (I see... She jumped in to help by acting like we were supposed to meet there.)
Kanade: No, I really appreciate what you did. Thank you...
Saki: Really? Thank goodness!
Saki: Also, Kanade... No, I did it again!
Saki: I'm really sorry. Ichi always calls you by your first name, and I think that's rubbed off on me...
Kanade: That's okay. You can call me by my first name if you like.
Saki: Really?! Thank you so much!
Saki: Then, umm...! Were you about to go somewhere, Kanade?
Kanade: Yes, I was thinking about going to the mall.
Saki: Oh, really? Me too!
Saki: I want to see what kinds of scarves they have since it's been so cold lately.
Kanade: Yes, it has been very cold...
Kanade: I'm thinking about buying a new jacket. Unfortunately, I poked a hole in my current one...
Saki: A new jacket...! That should be fun!
Kanade: Huh?
Saki: Isn't it exciting shopping for new clothes?
Saki: I always have so much fun thinking about which style to get and imagining how it's going to go with my current outfits...!
Kanade: It's fun to think about that...?
Kanade: I'm a little jealous, since I'm not all that particular when it comes to clothes...
Kanade: I do look for things that are easy to maintain and move around in, but...
Kanade: I almost prefer to just wear the clothes that other people recommend me.
Saki: I see...
Saki: Umm... You don't have to let me if you don't feel comfortable...
Saki: But can I help you pick out your new jacket?!
Kanade: Huh...?
